subSubSection.paragraph:
Distinguished from known congeners by combination of male cheliceral armature (
Fig. 77
), male palp (shapes of procursus and bulbal process; 
Figs 75, 76
), color pattern on prosoma and abdomen (
Figs 32- 35
), and epigynum with straight scape in anterior position and distinctive posterior structure (
Fig. 78
).

